---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="django">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    Django Tutorials
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      <strong class="text-custom-primary">Django</strong> is a high-level Python web framework that encourages rapid development and clean, pragmatic design. It follows the "batteries-included" philosophy and the DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principle.
    </p>

    <p>
      Django takes care of much of the hassle of web development, so you can focus on writing your app without needing to reinvent the wheel. It's free, open-source, and has a thriving community.
    </p>

    <p>
      In this tutorial series, you'll learn:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
      <li>Django project structure and setup</li>
      <li>Models and database design</li>
      <li>Views and URL routing</li>
      <li>Templates and frontend integration</li>
      <li>Forms and user input handling</li>
      <li>Authentication and admin interface</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Why Learn Django?</h2>
      <p>
        Django is one of the most popular and mature Python web frameworks. It's used by companies like Instagram, Pinterest, and Mozilla to build scalable web applications quickly.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        With built-in features for security, database management, and administration, Django allows developers to build robust web applications while following best practices out of the box.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>